SIMPLE: pry
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pry
<hw>Pry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted fr.
<ets>prize</ets> a lever. See <er>Prize</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>A lever; also, leverage.</def> <mark>[Local, U. S. &
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pry pole</b></col>, <cd>the pole which forms the prop of
a hoisting gin, and stands facing the windlass.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pry</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pry
<hw>Pry</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Pried</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Prying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To raise or move, or attempt to
raise or move, with a pry or lever; to prize.</def> <mark>[Local, U. S.
& Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pry</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pry
<hw>Pry</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>prien</ets>. Cf.
<er>Peer</er> to peep.]</ety> <def>To peep narrowly; to gaze; to inspect
closely; to attempt to discover something by a scrutinizing curiosity;
-- often implying reproach.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ To <xex>pry</xex> upon the
stars.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Watch thou and wake when others be asleep,⟦br⟧
To <qex>pry</qex> into the secrets of the state.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pry</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Pry
<hw>Pry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Curious inspection; impertinent
peeping.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pryan</ent>⟦br⟧
